  "content": "When dispatching actions in an editor, the second argument to `dispatch` is an `onErrors` callback invoked with any errors thrown by reducers processing the actions. This pattern supports displaying error messages to users, logging errors for debugging, and triggering recovery actions. Example: `dispatch(addTodoItem({ text }), (errors) => { alert(errors[0]?.message); });`",
